The paper deals with domination problems in circle graphs, which are a type of intersection graphs. This makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) the most likely category. The paper also discusses connectivity and acyclicity, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of parameterized complexity suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and geometric algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
